    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-01-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="305"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <head>305. Record of Actions Taken at the National Security Council Standing Group
                        Meeting<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d305fn0">Source: Department of
                            State,<gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 70 D 265, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                        Standing Group—January 26, 1962. Secret. No record of the <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Standing Group meeting has been
                        found.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-01-26">January 26, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follows Item 1 on Iran.]</p>
                <p>Item 2—<hi rend="italic">Status of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5704/3,
                        “U.S. Economic Defense Policy,” approved September 16, 1957</hi>,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d305fn1">Text in <ref target="frus1955-57v10#pg_495">Foreign
                            Relations, 1955–1957, vol. X, pp. 495</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1961-63v10#pg_498">498</ref>.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">and <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 2304-b,
                        approved October 5, 1960</hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d305fn2">Text <ref target="frus1958-60v04#pg_213">ibid.,
                            1958–1960, vol. IV, pp. 213</ref>–<ref target="frus1958-60v04#pg_214"
                            >214</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>(Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KFD1">Foy D. Kohler</persName>, Assistant Secretary of
                    State for European Affairs, was present for this Item.)</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(a)</label>
                    <item>Noted that the Secretary of State will initiate a review of the subject
                        policy paper with a view to its possible recision and replacement by a new
                        policy document.</item>
                    <label>(b)</label>
                    <item>Noted that the Secretary of State will circulate the Presidential
                        decisions taken following a recent meeting on export trade policy with
                        respect to licensing exports to the Soviet Bloc.<note n="3" xml:id="d305fn3"
                            >See <ref target="#d306fn1">footnote 1, Document 306</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>[Here follow Item 3 on Proposal of Communist China to Buy U.S. Wheat, Item 4 on
                    Albania, and Item 5 on Laos.]</p>
            </div>
